I"Ê<p>Improvements in fundamental human capabilities readily reverberate across the entirety of human capability. In light of this, Douglas Engelbart advocated that the development of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/tools-for-thought-interface-users-with-knowledge">tools for thought</a> should focus on the basics, resulting in a multiplexer-like amplification. How can the basic human skills be amplified, optimized, and augmented? This view is also consonant with <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-architecture-guides-cognitive-augmentation">the second brain framework for cognitive augmentation</a>, as it enables the engineer to focus on independent fundamental functions.</p>
